name: The Good, the Bad, and the Uncomfortable
Brother-in-Loss
summary: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr are forced to get cheeky with interviewers and explain their lackluster resumes while trying to land a job at a mobile company. Then, the guys head to the ferry where they piggyback one insane gesture on top of another. And tonight's loser bears witness to a matrimony that's anything but holy.

name: Welcome to Miami
summary: Meet Sal, Joe, Q, and Murr, four longtime friends who star in the hit truTV hidden camera show Impractical Jokers. In each episode, they compete to embarrass each other in a series of hilariously humiliating challenges and outrageous dares, all to the amusement and consternation of the general public. At the end of every episode, the biggest loser must endure a punishment of epic proportions. They have to say it. They have to do it. You have to see it!.

name: Damned If You Do
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q take it to the ice at LeFrak Center Ice Rink in Brooklyn for a slippery game that puts them all on the cutting edge of embarrassment. Then the guys head to the park where they try persuading New Yorkers to support some seriously ridiculous causes. And Murr, tonight's loser, relives the sins of his past with a captive audience when he's forced to sit through a screening and Q&A for the movie he made over 15 years ago and has tried to hide from the public ever since.

name: Bathroom Break
summary: The guys get sassy while posing as auto parts salesmen, then head to the mall where they try to reel in unsuspecting shoppers; tonight's big loser is stuck in a horrible mess after being locked inside a rigged bathroom of horrors.

name: Kill the Centaur
summary: The guys get ballsy while posing as salesmen, and then try to outdo each other as they invade the personal space of confused strangers.

name: Captain Fatbelly
summary: The guys lend an unhelpful hand while working at a high-tech store, then play detectives at the mall in search of perps on the loose.

name: Sneaking Number Twos, Going Number One
summary: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr play a game of "Put-Pocket" at a grocery store, then get jumpy at the park after taking over each other's cell phones. And tonight's big loser learns that when you gotta go...you gotta go.

name: Blind Justice
summary: The guys get a little punchy while giving boxing lessons, then head to the mall to share the gift of music with strangers. And when tonight's loser delivers the right speech to the wrong audience, he's the one who gets scared straight.

name: Tied and Feathered
summary: The guys teach a crash course in sorry behavior, ask strangers to settle bizarre debates, and spread surprisingly good news at the mall. Plus, tonight's loser has his hands tied when a day at the park turns into a frightful mess.

name: Smushed
summary: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr give a security presentation that's anything but safe, then hold hands with strangers in the park. And tonight's big loser quickly becomes an unwanted guest while clowning around at a kid's birthday party.

name: Anatomy of a Challenge
summary: Through four seasons of Impractical Jokers, the guys have never shied away from a challenge. Whether they're clipping balloons to strangers in a supermarket or pitching a humiliating autobiography to a focus group, Joe, Sal, Murr and Q do everything in their power to make each other squirm as much as humanly possible. In this special episode, the Jokers look back on the series' very best challenges and dish out behind-the-scenes secrets that have never been shared before.

name: Impractical Jokers: Unseen Scenes
summary: In this special episode, the Impractical Jokers unveil all the hilarity that was left on the cutting room floor. From unaired challenges to behind-the-scenes antics, the guys wax poetic about their favorite never-before-seen moments and give their fans a unique look behind the curtain.

name: Fan-tastic Countdown
summary: The Impractical Jokers count down the all-time greatest moments from the show, chosen by the fans! These are the most memorable bits - the iconic lines fans scream when they see the guys - the most shocking, cringe-worthy and embarrassing stunts that could only be pulled off by the Jokers. Essentially, it's a love letter to all the diehard fans; a crash course in why viewers love the guys so much. So let's get sexy and find Larry in the Castle Of White, Mustache! (If you don't get the references, you will after this special!)

name: 100th Episode: Punishment Special
summary: Sal, Joe, Q and Murr celebrate 100 episodes of Impractical Jokers with a LIVE punishment in the heart of NYC. Hosted by Howie Mandel, the hour-long special opens with pre-taped challenges that involve the guys crossing items off their bucket lists, faking injuries at the grocery store and making their glorious return to the infamous two-way mirror. The episode then shifts to South Street Seaport for a four-way punishment in which each Joker walks a five-story-high tightrope, live.

name: The Big Uneasy
summary: The guys visit New Orleans and steal sips from people's drinks at a bar, work with the wheel of voo-doom, and crash a horse and buggy ride.

name: Hopeless and Changeless
summary: The guys complete three assigned tasks at a greeting card store, fill in street-goers on their bizarre points of view, and give lessons on real estate.

name: Stripped of Dignity
summary: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr experience adventures in babysitting while asking reluctant strangers to watch their kid, then head to the grocery store to conduct taste(less) tests with shoppers. And tonight's big loser has all the wrong moves as he's forced to strip for all the wrong people.

name: HellCopter
summary: The guys pose as unreceptive receptionists, then head to a world famous wax museum; tonight's losers are taken on a chopper ride from hell.

name: You're Cut Off
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q earn stamps of disapproval while posing as employees at a copy center, then conduct bizarre exit interviews for moviegoers before hitting the streets with some peculiar protests. Later, it's Unhappy Hour for tonight's big loser, as he cuts off paying customers and quickly becomes the least popular guy at the party.

name: Ruffled Feathers
summary: The guys conduct focus groups to sell their illogical inventions created by the other guys, then head to a shoe store where they get off on the wrong foot. And tonight's big loser discovers he's more flight than fight at the zoo.

name: Stare Master
summary: The guys play a game of copycat at the park while babysitting kids. Then, they hit the supermarket for an epic battle of catch and release, and tonight's loser learns that creeping around the gym is more uncomfortable than working out.

name: Bidder Loser
summary: The guys ask strangers to help them bury bizarre items, then try to cling onto strangers' cars, and tonight's big loser makes enemies at an auction house.

name: The Good, the Bad and the Punished
summary: The guys pose as cranky NY cab drivers, then solicit undeserved congrats in the park; tonight's loser is sheriff of an old Nevada town.

name: Putting the P in Pool
summary: The guys pose as crummy cashiers at a grocery store and then play with laser pointers at a mall; a loser gets soaked with embarrassment.

name: Statue of Limitations
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q greet customers at a restaurant while posing as inhospitable hosts, then beg strangers to babysit their grandfathers at the mall. And later, it's a top secret mission as tonight's big loser unknowingly endures the longest punishment in the history of Impractical Jokers.

name: Brother of the Sisterhood
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q cast each other as helpless oddballs in a waiting room, then head to the grocery store to convince shoppers to give them cash they clearly don't deserve. And later, the feminist movement is set back decades when tonight's big loser poses as an expert on women's issues.

name: Dark Side of the Moon
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q make bizarre passes at supermarket shoppers, then pose as roving reporters asking insane questions written by the other guys. And tonight's big loser is the butt of the joke after being prescribed a painfully invasive punishment.

name: Whose Phone is Ringing?
summary: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr hit a bull's-eye while going face-to-face at a clothing store, and then try to undermine each other in a focus group where sabotage is the name of the game. Then, tonight's big loser crashes a classy book reading, and quickly learns that silence is indeed golden.

name: Centaur of Attention
summary: Murr, Joe, Sal and Q go head-to-head in a focus group, trying to undermine each other at every turn. Then they spread some confusion at a bagel store before heading to the park where they hit all the wrong notes. Finally, tonight's big loser gets hunted down during a truly humiliating walk of shame.

name: Browbeaten
summary: Sal, Q, Murr and Joe take name-calling to new, hilarious heights while playing receptionists. Then the guys hit a pizza shop, begging customers for donations to some half-baked charities. And in tonight's punishment, one Joker loses more than just his dignity when the other three guys give him an epic shave that's too close for comfort.

name: The Coward
summary: Joe, Sal, Murr and Q show who's the boss while working the counter at a fast food joint, and then whisper sweet nothings to grocery store customers, looking for a little something in return. Then, tonight's big loser assists a cow in labor, and nearly winds up buying the farm.

name: Virtual Insanity
summary: The guys bark up the wrong tree at a pet store; tonight's big loser virtually loses his mind after entering a world he's never visited before.

name: Laundry Day
summary: The guys are on the prowl for partners in crime at a supermarket, and then throw caution to the wind as helpless romantics in the park. Later, tonight's big loser adds some pep to an arena football game, treating the crowd to a wardrobe malfunction they'll never forget.

name: Water Torture
summary: Joe, Q, Sal and Murr spin a wheel and hope for the best while creeping out shoppers at the mall. Then, the guys get what they deserve at a coffee shop, and it all leads to an impromptu punishment that leaves one Joker soaked, enraged, and totally shocked.

name: Hitting the Wrong Note
summary: Joe, Sal, Q and Murr dress to the nines, but act like zeroes while trying to get sympathy for their problems. Then, a video game focus group goes off the rails, and tonight's big loser faces the music in a tone-deaf punishment that gets lost in translation.

name: Heckle and Hide
summary: Heckle and Hide: Q, Murr, Sal and Joe ask strangers for a little help with some big items at the grocery store, and share their hot entrepreneurial tips with a group of poor unfortunate souls. Finally, tonight's big loser strikes out while posing as "that dad" at a little league softball game.

name: The Chairman
summary: The Chairman: The guys shock shoppers by going footloose and fancy-free in a discount store, then pose insane questions to strangers in the park. And tonight's big loser is taken for a wild ride in a tricked-out wheelchair he can't possibly control.

name: Wrapper's Delight
summary: Wrapper's Delight: Murr, Joe, Sal and Q make a mockery of each other while acting as restaurant managers, sing along with strangers trying to name that (made up) tune, and then head to the park for some awkward fun in the sun. Then tonight's big loser gets wrapped up in a birthday surprise that definitely wasn't on his wish list.

name: Training Day
summary: The guys go to a supermarket with bells on and try to reminisce with strangers in the park; the three losers are put through an epic trial by fire.

name: Nitro Circus Spectacular
summary: The guys tackle their biggest challenges yet, including two high-stakes live punishments and a four-part obstacle course.
